title: UEFA leaders demand answers on Platini payment at meeting
text: > Top News UEFA leaders demand answers on Platini payment at meeting German Karl-Heinz Rummenigge, CEO of FC Bayern Munich soccer club, arrives during the meeting of the UEFA Executive Committee and the meeting of UEFA's 54 member associations at the UEFA headquarters in Nyon, Switzerland, Thursday, Oct. 15, 2015. UEFA leaders are meeting to decide whether to continue backing Michel Platini, with some not yet satisfied by his explanation for a payment that led to his 90-day FIFA suspension. (Jean-Christophe Bott/Keystone via AP)
